WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Smaller transit agencies are stuck with a stack of tools that don't talk to each other.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Census data lives in one place, your routes in another.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Title VI compliance gets cobbled together every year from scratch.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
GTFS·X consolidates this into one browser-based tool.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
You can analyze operating costs for your system or by route,

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:27.000
or analyze stop spacing and identify closely spaced stops that are reducing vehicle operating speeds,

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.000
and even identify candidate stops to optimize your route.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
You can quantify your system coverage.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:38.000
How many people does your system serve, and what are their demographics?

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:44.000
And Title VI analysis is now as easy as a click of a button.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:50.000
To plan your service, demand dots show where there may be unmet demand for service.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Creating new routes is quick and easy.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:57.000
You draw your route, and then add stops.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:06.000
You can use the timetable panel to automatically estimate vehicle run times between stops.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Then use this to build a complete trip table based on your headways.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
With your trip table built, you can analyze service costs,

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:25.000
or even estimate the demographics of the riders it covers.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:30.000
The tool also supports scenario analysis to compare alternatives side by side.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Choose your route alternatives to define a scenario,

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:38.000
then switch between scenarios using the scenario dropdown.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:43.000
You can compare your scenarios and pick the one that wins on cost,

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:47.000
or perhaps pick the one that wins on equity.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Book a demo today to see how GTFS·X can simplify your planning and feed management.
